btained a <strong>European certificate as a fire protection equipment company</strong> outside the Flemish Region can also obtain the Flemish recognition certificate as a fire protection equipment company. However, the company must register with the Flemish administration before starting to work in the Flemish Region.</p><h2><strong>Validity period and obligations</strong></h2><p>Recognition as a fire protection equipment company is valid for an <strong>indefinite period</strong>. Your company must meet the following obligations, among others, to retain recognition:</p><ul><li>duly and fully complete <strong>the installation log book</strong></li><li>ensure that recognised fire protection equipment technicians are deployed for work subject to recognition</li><li>hold <strong>insurance </strong>for third party liability, including professional liability, in connection with the use of the recognition</li><li>report any changes in the identification details (such as address, e-mail address) immediately via <a href=\"mailto:erkenningen.omgeving@vlaanderen.be\">erkenningen.omgeving@vlaanderen.be</a></li><li>pay the <a href=\"https://www.uat-vlaanderen.be/vlarel-retributies\">annual fee</a> for the supervision of the recognition. The first payment must be made in the year following the year in which the fire protection equipment company has obtained the Flemish recognition certificate. Failure to pay the annual fee will lead to automatic suspension of the recognition following a formal notice of default. If the fee is still not paid within 30 days of the suspension, the recognition will automatically lapse.</li></ul><p>More <a href=\"https://omgeving.vlaanderen.be/informatie-voor-erkende-bedrijven-brandbeveiligingsapparatuur\">information on the obligations of fire protection equipment companies</a> is available on the Department of Environment and Spatial Development website.</p>","nl":"<p>Om erkend te worden als <strong>bedrijf brandbeveiligingsapparatuur</strong>, moet